20just%20heard%20mumbling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20one%20layoff%20shifted%20my%20whole%20perception%20of%20work.%20Instead%20of%20taking%20job%20security%20for%20granted%2C%20it's%20forced%20me%20to%20never%20get%20too%20comfortable%20and%20always%20invest%20in%20myself%20and%20my%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20life%20would%20probably%20have%20been%20more%20fun%20if%20I%20weren't%20constantly%20thinking%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-hr-manager-got-laid-off-too-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egetting%20laid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20am%20well%20prepared%20if%20it%20happens%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2223a76527-bac1-49a3-8424-38b426d63141%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20new%20job%20after%20the%20layoff%20was%20quite%20easy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20when%20the%20layoff%20happened%2C%20they%20gave%20me%20notice%2C%20so%20I%20had%20time%20to%20look%20for%20new%20jobs%2C%20as%20well%20as%20eight%20weeks%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-employee-reviews-choose-pip-or-severance-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseverance%20pay%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20a%20new%20job%20before%20my%20last%20day.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20new%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20quite%20easy.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20computer%20science%20graduates%20from%20reputable%20universities%20could%20practically%20walk%20into%20interviews%20and%20get%20jobs.%20I%20got%20two%20offers%20and%20chose%20a%20software%20engineering%20job%20at%20Home%20Depot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20at%20Home%20Depot%20for%20about%20six%20years%20before%20switching%20to%20my%20current%20company%20in%202022.%20I'm%20still%20in%20software%20engineering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d85aac73-9271-4932-b578-97e0b19faa65%5C%22%3EEvery%20veteran%20software%20engineer%20I've%20met%20has%20lost%20a%20job%20before%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20laid%20off%20removed%20my%20internal%20sense%20of%20security.%20As%20someone%20who%20went%20to%20a%20good%20school%20and%20did%20the%20right%20internship%2C%20I%20prepared%20and%20worked%20hard%20to%20get%20to%20this%20point%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20guarantee%20a%20good%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20questioned%20why%20I%20was%20let%20go%20or%20if%20I%20wasn't%20smart%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecent-company-layoffs-laying-off-workers-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20part%20of%20life.%20I've%20yet%20to%20meet%20a%20software%20engineer%20who's%20been%20in%20the%20industry%20for%20over%2015%20years%20who%20hasn't%20experienced%20some%20kind%20of%20job%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20it%20still%20affected%20my%20mindset.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20I've%20seen%20the%20prevalence%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-layoffs-january-versus-first-half-2022-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%20in%20tech%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20made%20me%20want%20to%20put%20more%20effort%20into%20growing%20my%20side%20ventures%2C%20so%20that%20if%20something%20were%20to%20happen%20to%20my%20job%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20start%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e3e11176-41b5-4d7d-b302-0f9b179b58e1%5C%22%3EI%20don't%20feel%20secure%20in%20a%20job%20anymore%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20to%20do%20three%20job%20interviews%20a%20year%2C%20not%20necessarily%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20getting%20a%20new%20job%2C%20but%20to%20keep%20my%20interview%20skills%20up-to-date.%20If%20I%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-during-pregnancy-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20start%20preparing%20for%20interviews%20under%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I've%20thought%20about%20taking%20a%20new%20job%2C%20I've%20tried%20to%20consider%20how%20the%20company%20makes%20money%20and%20how%20financially%20secure%20they%20are.%20I'm%20more%20careful%20about%20what%20opportunities%20I%20say%20yes%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20try%20not%20to%20spend%20too%20much%20money.%20I%20never%20know%20when%20the%20rug%20will%20be%20pulled%20from%20under%20my%20feet.%20I%20put%20effort%20into%20my%20401(k)%2C%20investing%2C%20and%20I%20have%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20support%20myself%20for%20at%20least%20six%20months%20if%20I%20lose%20a%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20take%20extravagant%20trips%2C%20even%20though%20I%20can%20afford%20them%2C%20because%20I'm%20trying%20to%20play%20it%20safe%20financially.%20I%20only%20started%20traveling%20outside%20the%20country%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20visit%20places%20that%20are%20cheaper%20to%20fly%20to%2C%20like%20the%20Caribbean.%20I%20don't%20splurge%20on%20nicer%20things%2C%20like%20first-class%20plane%20tickets%20or%20nice%20hotels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2211a7c70b-787e-4e7e-adb6-0bfb0e3c710f%5C%22%3EI%20developed%20a%20fear%20that%20having%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20isn't%20enough%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20I%20enrolled%20in%20a%20master's%20program%20in%20computer%20science%2C%20graduating%20in%202023.%20The%20only%20thing%20I%20can%20control%20is%20to%20invest%20in%20my%20own%20education%20and%20skillset%2C%20so%20I%20feel%20that%20I%20have%20backup%20plans%20if%20something%20goes%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20also%20been%20investing%20in%20side%20ventures.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20run%20a%20YouTube%20channel%20and%20I%20work%20as%20a%20freelancer%20helping%20small%20businesses%20with%20tech%20problems.%20These%20aren't%20my%20primary%20