or%20in%20these%20situations%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20being%20the%20consummate%20gold-star%20student%20in%20the%20group%20project%20in%20school%20who's%20the%20only%20one%20carrying%20everybody%20else's%20weight%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20a%20good%20sign%20that%20you%20need%20to%20reset%20some%20of%20those%20dynamics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225642e31d-1f95-4267-8376-46ee76ccc9fa%5C%22%3EStarting%20is%20the%20hardest%20part%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESetting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-create-boundaries-at-work-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethat%20first%20boundary%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%2C%20can%20be%20tricky%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20time%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-layoffs-quit-jobs-hybrid-remote-work-office-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elayoffs%20and%20restructurings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilding%20has%20had%20clients%20who%20told%20her%20they%20thought%20they%20were%20doing%20the%20right%20thing%20by%20working%20overtime%20and%20handling%20dozens%20of%20projects%20outside%20their%20job%20requirements%20%E2%80%94%20only%20to%20be%20told%20at%20their%20performance%20review%20they%20were%20struggling%20to%20balance%20all%20their%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20client%20described%20themselves%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20spray%20foam%26quot%3B%20filling%20in%20%26quot%3Ball%20the%20cracks%20for%20everyone%20else%26quot%3B%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20may%20think%20we're%20doing%20the%20right%20thing%2C%20but%20in%20actuality%20it%20can%20create%20this%20perception%20that%20we%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20manage%20our%20time%2C%20that%20we%20are%20not%20leadership%20material%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilding%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20the%20ultimate%20punch%20in%20the%20gut.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20moving%20up%2C%20people%20get%20stuck%20because%20so%20many%20others%20in%20the%20company%20are%20overly%20dependent%20on%20them%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BOf%20course%20it%20leads%20to%20more%20resentment%2C%20it%20leads%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburnout-work-boss-left-office-on-stretcher-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eburnout%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20exhaustion%2C%20and%20it%20becomes%20this%20vicious%20cycle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226922a457-652c-429e-90d6-4a40e9cc0490%5C%22%3EDo%20it%20for%20your%20future%20self%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20feeling%20of%20someone%20pushing%20back%20on%20our%20boundaries%20also%20runs%20along%20the%20same%20pathways%20in%20the%20brain%20as%20physical%20pain%2C%20Wilding%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20someone%20who%20has%20been%20overly%20accommodating%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20feel%20really%20uncomfortable%20to%20put%20up%20boundaries.%20You're%20going%20to%20feel%20guilty%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20feel%20as%20if%20I'm%20doing%20something%20bad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20just%20your%20brain%20tricking%20you%2C%20in%20Wilding's%20view.%20When%20sitting%20in%20this%20discomfort%2C%20she%20recommends%20asking%20yourself%20what%20your%20future%20self%20will%20thank%20you%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThree%20months%20from%20now%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%20really%20happy%20I%20didn't%20commit%20to%20this%20three-day%20retreat%20with%20my%20team%2C%20even%20if%20I%20feel%20a%20bit%20bad%20in%20the%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoundaries%20lie%20on%20a%20spectrum.%20Some%20are%20rigid%2C%20like%20a%20fence%20or%20a%20wall%20with%20no%20holes%20in%20it%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20can%20get%20in%2C%20but%20nothing%20can%20get%20out%20either%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilding%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20opposite%20end%20are%20very%20porous%20boundaries%20that%20have%20huge%20gaps%20allowing%20anything%20to%20get%20in%20and%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHealthy%20boundaries%20are%20right%20in%20the%20middle%20where%20we%20have%20certain%20non-negotiables%20or%20limits%20that%20we%20want%20to%20stand%20firm%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilding%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20you're%20willing%20to%20be%20responsive%20to%20the%20moment%2C%20to%20the%20person%2C%20to%20the%20situation%2C%20and%20the%20circumstances%20of%20that%20request.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20not%20being%20too%20accommodating%20or%20too%20uncompromising%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bstriking%20that%20sort%20of%20Goldilocks%20right%20in%20the%20middle%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220989b3af-753e-44ca-be01-36c13496b26e%5C%22%3EBoundaries%20can%20boost%20productivity%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20good%20first%20boundary%20to%20put%20in%20place%20can%20be%20to%20protect%20your%20focus%20time%2C%20Wilding%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Binstead%20of%20just%20yet%20another%20meeting%20or%20yet%20another%20check-in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20be%20more%20specific%20with%20your%20status%20updates%20on%20Slack%20or%20Teams%20to%20give%20people%20an%20expectation%20of%20what%20you're%20doing%20and%20when%20you'll%20be%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSay%2C%20'I'm%20heads%20down%20in%20the%20budget%20until%202%20p.m.%20and%20will%20respond%20to%20messages%20after%20that'.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrame%20it%20in%20terms%20of%20what's%20in%20it%20for%20them%2C%20Wilding%20added%2C%20rather%20than%20asking%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoing%20forward%2C%20I%20will%20be%20blocking%20out%20two%20hours%20each%20week%20on%20Friday%20in%20order%20to%20work%20on%20this%20project%20that%20I%20know%20is%20important%20to%20our%20Q3%20goals%2C%26quot%3B%20Wilding%20suggested.%20%26quot%3BSet%20them%20in%20the%20affirmative%2C%20so%20basically%20say%20what%20you%20can%20do%2C%20versus%20what%20you%20won't%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20good%20business%20case%20for%20a%20culture%20where%20boundaries%20are%20celebrate