ger%20deal%20on%20TVs%2C%20big%20brand%20deals%20can%20help%20the%20platform%20improve%20the%20production%20value%20of%20its%20shows%20without%20paying%20upfront%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20is%20picking%20shows%20for%20its%20cultural%20moments%20packages%20that%20look%20like%20traditional%20TV%2C%20where%20it%20knows%20people%20tune%20in%20for%20those%20live%20events.%20Hartbeat%20makes%20shows%20specifically%20for%20YouTube%20but%20also%20makes%20cinematic%20entertainment%20for%20streamers%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20advertisers%20will%20buy%20in%20is%20an%20open%20question.%20Some%20are%20still%20unconvinced%20that%20YouTube%20content%20is%20on%20par%20with%20traditional%20TV.%20Two%20top%20video%20ad%20buyers%20told%20BI%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20other%20places%20to%20buy%20into%20the%20cultural%20conversation%2C%20so%20YouTube's%20pitch%20is%20hardly%20unique.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvertisers%20who%20can%20afford%20to%20buy%20ads%20around%20the%20actual%20sports%20content%20may%20be%20less%20interested%20in%20a%20creator's%20spin%20on%20it.%20However%2C%20for%20those%20with%20smaller%20budgets%20who%20value%20YouTube's%20audience%2C%20its%20pitch%20could%20be%20attractive%2C%20one%20of%20the%20buyers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20YouTube's%20pitch%20succeeds%20with%20bigger%20advertisers%2C%20it%20could%20broaden%20creators'%20access%20to%20advertisers%20and%20revenue.%20Except%20for%20the%20top%20level%2C%20YouTube%20creators%20often%20don't%20have%20direct%20relationships%20with%20blue-chip%20advertisers.%20Those%20who%20get%20chosen%20for%20%26quot%3Bcultural%26quot%3B%20sponsorships%2C%20as%20YouTube%20calls%20them%2C%20would%20also%20get%20extra%20exposure%20on%20a%20dedicated%20hub%20to%20help%20them%20get%20discovered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20our%20top%20creators%20have%20their%20own%20teams%20that%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20source%20brand%20partnerships%20for%20years.%20We've%20been%20facilitating%20these%20connections%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Albert%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20new%20now%20is%20just%20the%20fact%20that%20we're%20wrapping%20it%20around%20this%20cultural%20moments'%20calendar.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-is-trying-to-ahead-of-netflix-advertising-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748334781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683088ec6ffb6822ec615790%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-is-trying-to-ahead-of-netflix-advertising-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20Hollywood%20warms%20up%20to%20creators%2C%20a%20YouTube%20exec%20described%20how%20its%20sponsorships%20pitch%20can%20benefit%20creators.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmoses%40insider.com%20(Lucia%20Moses)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-is-trying-to-ahead-of-netflix-advertising-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20former%20top%20Meta%20exec%20says%20AI%20is%20doomed%20if%20artists%20want%20tech%20firms%20to%20ask%20for%20permission%20to%20train%20models%20on%20their%20work%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224485%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nick%20Clegg%20speaking%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20Hanoi%2C%20Vietnam.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68352f99ca50259add4d09b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222990%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20don't%20know%20how%20you%20go%20around%2C%20asking%20everyone%20first.%20I%20just%20don't%20see%20how%20that%20would%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nick%20Clegg%2C%20who%20left%20Meta%20in%20January.%3Cp%3ENhac%20Nguyen%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EClegg%20was%20Meta's%20president%20of%20global%20affairs.%20He%20left%20the%20company%20in%20January.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClegg%20said%20it%20would%20be%20tough%20for%20companies%20to%20ask%20artists%20before%20training%20models%20on%20their%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20this%20would%20%26quot%3Bbasically%20kill%20the%20AI%20industry%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20executive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprofile-nick-clegg-rise-meta-facebook-zuckerberg-inner-circle-politics-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENick%20Clegg%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20the%20UK's%20AI%20industry%20will%20be%20killed%20if%20tech%20companies%20must%20ask%20artists%20for%20permission%20to%20use%20their%20work%20when%20training%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClegg%20was%20promoting%20his%20upcoming%20book%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20Save%20the%20Internet%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20Charleston%20Festival%20on%20Thursday%20when%20he%20was%20asked%20about%20artists'%20demands%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-copyright-laws-big-tech-fair-use-openai-meta-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etighter%20AI%20copyright%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClegg%20said%20it%20would%20be%20reasonable%20to%20let%20artists%20%26quot%3Bopt%20out%20of%20having%20their%20creativity%2C%20their%20products%2C%20what%20they've%20worked%20on%20indefinitely%20modeled.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20said%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20implausible%26quot%3B%20if%20they%20expect%20companies%20to%20get%20permission%20before%20training%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClegg%20said%20this%20is%20because%20%26quot%3Bthese%20systems%20train%20on%20vast%20amounts%20of%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20don't%20know%20how%20you%20go%20around%2C%20asking%20everyone%20first.%20I%20just%20don't%20see%20how%20that%20would%20work.%20And%20by%20the%20way%2C%20if%20you%20did%20it%20in%20Britain%20and%20no%20one%20else%20did%20it%2C%20you%20would%20basically%20kill%20the%20AI%20industry%20in%20this%20country%20overnight%2C%26quot%3B%20Clegg%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClegg%20was%20the%20UK's%20deputy%20prime%20minister%20from%202010%20to%202015.%20He%20joined%20Meta%20in%202018%20as%20its%20vice%20president%20for%20global%20affairs%20and%20communications%20and%20was%20promoted%20to%20president%20of%20global%20affairs%20in%202022.%20He%20announced%20his%20departure%20from%20Meta%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClegg%20and%20representatives%20for%20Meta%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20the%20UK%20government%20introduced%20the%20Data%20(Use%20and%20Access)%20Bill.%20The%20bill%20will%20allow%20companies%20to%20train%20AI%20on%20creative%20works%20such%20as%20books%20and%20music%2C%20unless%20the%20copyright%20holder%20opts%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%20voted%20to%20amend%20the%20bill%20to%20require%20tech%20companies%20to%20disclose%20and%20seek%20consent%20before%20using%20copyrighted%20material%20to%20train%20their%20models.%20The%20House%20of%20Commons%20rejected%20the%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESinger%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felton-john-lost-eyesight-premiere-new-musical-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElton%20John%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20the%20BBC%20on%20May%2018%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felton-john-uk-government-ai-legislation-artists-copyright-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Every%20angry%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20bill%2C%20as%20it%20would%20allow%20tech%20companies%20to%20engage%20in%20%26quot%3Btheft%2C%20thievery%20on%20a%20high%20scale.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20he%20was%20prepared%20to%20take%20the%20government